Find Hot French Food Near Me: A Follow-upPublished on September 6, 2023 12:32 PM GMT<br/><br/><p> On <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/D5urD7WmDePyii73D/who-has-the-best-food">Zvi&#39;s recent post</a> about French food I posted an <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/D5urD7WmDePyii73D/?commentId=Lzja5wcSSjSh4gSoG">inflammatory comment</a> (saying in essence that French food is so bad American capitalism hasn&#39;t even bothered stealing it).  I got <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/D5urD7WmDePyii73D/who-has-the-best-food?commentId=8m4kxgkiZpghFkior">challenged</a> to provide evidence supporting this, and particularly to back up my claim that there were more German than French restaurants near me.</p><p>正确的。是的。 Evidence. I am a reasonable adult who understands that beliefs must be supported by evidence.所以。 Here we go.</p><h1> Some Google Searches</h1><p> I&#39;ve searched for &#39;[ethnicity] restaurant near Grove Street, Jersey City, NJ&#39; (I live in Jersey City, and the Grove Street area is reasonably near the center).</p><p> When I search for &#39;French&#39; I can count 13 results: </p><figure class="image"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/youhinoozrt4u1xwg57q" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/wbtdmbt8g4a5xhyspytd 115w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/mkszgmmoor6revnaeuol 195w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/x0a5crvfus3qb9ebvmul 275w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/csyalzzehxmzlzdphjyj 355w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/fmbavdelmiuhsfeax6uv 435w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/pgitgnxodrjzgunok37c 515w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/bbb21hhvktrzzujglhgq 595w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/ikaifxqrezbdhrmjhqws 675w"></figure><p></p><p> And when I search for &#39;German&#39; I count only 9: </p><figure class="image"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/piqytlnxzfganabmvqfv" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/d7ghev85h3ozn8drvjig 157w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/repaldxfwb5yts6ck8un 237w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/cl1ltpaba53u2rjynaxa 317w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/vv8p3ibibugykp1e3qz4 397w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/opzsw9gztkeriivwqf31 477w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/ebv6xpbzif5gj7ghmref 557w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/chwespgvva16kvprebqx 637w"></figure><p>哈！ The foolish American has been hoisted on his own petard! (&#39;Petard&#39; is French for &#39;fuck you&#39;).</p><p> Perhaps unsurprisingly, I don&#39;t think these numbers tell the whole story.</p><h1> What Makes These Places French?</h1><p> Google&#39;s definition of &#39;French&#39; and &#39;German&#39; restaurants here appears to be <strong>extremely expansive.</strong></p><ul><li> <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/u6sr26nW7AwmbABa6">Hudson Hound Jersey City</a> , an &#39;Irish gastropub&#39;, shows up on the French search.</li><li> <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/2XnZtAHLVeDvdqiQ8">Shadman</a> , a &#39;go-to for Pakistani and Indian cuisine&#39;, shows up on the German search.</li><li> <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/7vwWsxpkmCLZ7z3FA">Luna</a> , for &#39;Italian eats&#39;, shows up on the French search.</li><li> <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/kk4Z7v6GSAXvq4iL7">Frankie</a> , an &#39;Australian eatery&#39;, shows up on the German search.</li></ul><p> So, for lack of anything better to do, I&#39;ve gone through manually to look for things that I think &#39;count&#39; as French or German.</p><p> The two &#39;real&#39; German places (and the ones I was thinking of in my comment) are <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/3swQDMosRiEcKaTV8">&#39;Wurstbar&#39;</a> and <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/PihP6NdCrJbQ7TXa8">&#39;Zeppelin Hall Beer Garden&#39;</a> , and while we may question the taste of these places I do not think we can question their German-ness.  The search also turned up &#39; <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/JXje9RqMUQFCJafv5">Hudson Hall</a> &#39;, a &#39;Euro beer bar with house-smoked meats&#39;, which I think at least ambiguously might count.</p><p> It&#39;s less clear to me how many of the hits for &#39;French restaurant&#39; are actually both French and restaurants.  Certainly I&#39;ve been to a few of these places, and none of them have charged me twenty-three dollars for a baguette while sneering at me.  We have:</p><ul><li> Cafe Madelaine describes itself as a French restaurant.  We count that.</li><li> Choc O Pain definitely sounds French, but it&#39;s not clear to me if it&#39;s actually a restaurant: it seems to actually be a bakery, and the <a href="https://www.chocopainbakery.com/s/shop">menu</a> seems to bear that out.  I&#39;ll give it half.</li><li> Hudson Hound self-describes as &#39;Irish&#39;.</li><li> Matthews Food and Drink self-describes as &#39;American&#39; (though I guess it also self-describes as &#39;chic&#39;).</li><li> Grove Station self-describes as &#39;New American&#39; (I have no idea what that means).</li><li> El Sazon De Las Americas self-describes as &#39;Dominican&#39; (I don&#39;t think that counts as French, though I&#39;m sure someone will make the case).</li><li> Uncle Momo self-describes as &#39;French-Lebanese fare&#39;.  Let&#39;s give that half again.</li><li> Beechwood Cafe self-describes as &#39;American&#39;.</li><li> Luna self-describes as &#39;Italian&#39;.</li><li> Razza is an Italian pizza place.</li><li> Short Grain is...uh...a &#39;hip place with sidewalk seats serving Asian-influenced &amp; vegetarian dishes, plus coffee &amp; green tea&#39;, and while I have no idea what that is and don&#39;t particularly want to find out I don&#39;t think it means &#39;French&#39;.</li><li> Frankie self-describes as &#39;Italian&#39;.</li><li> Cafe Dolma self-describes as &#39;Greek&#39;.</li></ul><p> So overall I think &#39;French&#39; and &#39;German&#39; each end up with either 2 or 3 restaurants, depending on how you count some edge cases.</p><h1>概括</h1><p>I am sorry that I said French food was not as successful under capitalism as German food.  I see now that French food is <strong>exactly</strong> as popular and successful as German food, and I&#39;ll fight anyone who says otherwise!</p><br/><br/> <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/find-hot-french-food-near-me-a-follow-up#comments">讨论</a>; https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZ/find-hot-french-food-near-me-a-follow-up Gv2yv4idk6Hcas8vZaphyer Wed, 06 Sep 2023 12:32:03 GMT 
